22,IssuesEvent,2017-04-12 17:21:06+00:00,8387179,uiri/toml,364765,uiri,,,closed,floats with exponents outputted with leading 0s,[],[],1,"Floats with exponents with leading `0`s (such as `1e-05`) are outputted with the leading `0` still attached, which is apparently not allowed under a strict interpretation of the toml spec. Float exponent fields are int fields, which are not allowed to have leading `0`s.

The problem comes from other toml parsers which take this (too?) seriously (for instance https://github.com/alexcrichton/toml-rs) and fail to load output generated by this lib

Is there any easy way to override the default formatting for a certain type?
",{},{}
