395,IssuesEvent,2017-02-01 05:51:44+00:00,10074815,berdario/pew,5271761,nateprewitt,,,opened,Which pythonz does pew use?,[],[],0,"pew seems to be unable to install via `pip`/`setuptools` on Python 2.6 because the dependency `pythonz` has an incompatible setup.py. It uses the format function without specifying parameter order inside the curly brackets (e.g. `{0} {1}`) which wasn't supported until 2.7.

I'm happy to submit a PR to fix this but wanted to know where the current repository is. It looks like you maintain a fork which is what the PyPI page points to. However, it doesn't appear to have been updated in a while, the original has recently been updated but isn't compatible with PyPIs infrastructure anymore.

Any comment on which direction to pursue would be greatly appreciated. Thanks!",{},{}
