1953,IssuesEvent,2017-09-11 19:47:56+00:00,3489194,davidhalter/jedi,748594,davidhalter,,,closed,No completions for class members in certain circumstances,"[{'id': 17235917, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/davidhalter/jedi/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'e10c02', 'default': True}]",[],1,"I'm not sure what exactly is causing this, but in certain situations I'm not getting completions on class members.  Here's a minimal test case:

``` python
from typing import List            

class A(object):                   
    def __init__(self, name: str): 
        self.name = name           

class B(object):                   
    def __init__(self, a: List[A]):
        self.a = a                 

class C(object):                   
    def use_b(self, b: B):         
        for a in b.a:  # b.a completes as expected
            print(a.name)  # but no completion for a.name

def main():                        
    b = B(list([A('name')]))
    for a in b.a:                  
        print(a.name)  # a.name completes here as expected

if __name__ == '__main__':         
    main()                         
```

I verified that this is happening on several different commits, including `master`, back to 66557903.
",{},{}
