2535,IssuesEvent,2018-04-08 20:28:06+00:00,74618801,halcy/Mastodon.py,315139,codl,,,opened,should StreamListener keep track of heartbeats and close stream if n of them are missed?,[],[],0,"If a client goes offline for a while then comes back online, the StreamListener will keep the stream open even though the server at the other end has already closed the connection. While an application *can* listen for heartbeats and do its own checks, that logic is going to be the same in every application. It's also a bit counter-intuitive.

I propose that, at least by default, StreamListener should close the stream after 5 minutes. Or a configurable length of time. I'm not sure how often heartbeats are sent",{},{}
