3165,IssuesEvent,2018-07-29 02:41:13+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,16495887,doakey3,,,opened,"Local Hyperlinks, Documentation demo",[],[],0,"I am trying to create a hyperlink to another slide in the same presentation.

From the [documentation on hyperlinks](https://python-pptx.readthedocs.io/en/latest/dev/analysis/txt-hyperlink.html), I understand I need to create a run like this:

``` python
    from pptx import Presentation

    filepath = 'test.pptx'
    pres = Presentation(filepath)
    slide = pres.slides[0]
    paragraph = slide.shapes[0].text_frame.paragraphs[0]

    run = paragraph.add_run()
    run.text = ""hello world""
    font = run.font
    run.hyperlink.address = 'https://github.com/scanny/python-pptx'
```

The documentation is a bit hard for me to understand regarding how to create a hyperlink to a target within the PowerPoint file itself. The quote from the documentation is:

> Hyperlinks in PowerPoint can have four types of targets: ....
> another part in the same presentation. This uses an internal relationship (in the .rels item) to the target part.

Can you describe in detail how to create a target using the .rels item and how to hyperlink to that target? Thanks!",{},{}
