3285,IssuesEvent,2018-02-09 00:49:00+00:00,65155092,ClimbsRocks/auto_ml,7017045,ClimbsRocks,,,closed,lgbm max_bin parameter will be deprecated,[],[],1,"I haven't actually used lgbm in ```auto_ml``` myself yet and only see this error in my own prototype code, but this seems like an optimization issue that will creep up in ```auto_ml```.

It looks like ```max_bin``` parameter in lgbm is deprecated and has no affect on the grid search for lgbm models. If you try passing in max_bin as a parameter to an LGBMClassifier object and run a fit, you get this message:
```
/home/ubuntu/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/lightgbm/basic.py:642: UserWarning: max_bin keyword has been found in `params` and will be ignored. Please use max_bin argument of the Dataset constructor to pass this parameter.
  'Please use {0} argument of the Dataset constructor to pass this parameter.'.format(key))
/home/ubuntu/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/lightgbm/basic.py:648: LGBMDeprecationWarning: The `max_bin` parameter is deprecated and will be removed in 2.0.12 version. Please use `params` to pass this parameter.
  'Please use `params` to pass this parameter.', LGBMDeprecationWarning)
```

I think this parameter can only be set in lightgbm.Dataset: http://lightgbm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Python-API.html

Which isn't really accessible from the LGBMClassifier and LGBMRegressor sklearn wrappers, I think they construct the Dataset objects from the X and y input.",{},{}
