4441,IssuesEvent,2017-06-03 15:13:47+00:00,24561828,gunthercox/ChatterBot,2030578,gunthercox,,,closed,Run SQL tests in memory,"[{'id': 491806208, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gunthercox/ChatterBot/labels/testing', 'name': 'testing', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],2,"It would be optimal if the tests for the SQL adapter could be run with the database in memory. This would have better performance and make cleanup easier. Sqlite does support this.

**From the documentation (http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/core/engines.html):**

To use a SQLite `:memory:` database, specify an empty URL:
```python
engine = create_engine('sqlite://')
```",{},{}
