5112,IssuesEvent,2016-10-19 08:05:22+00:00,9376661,lorenzofox3/Smart-Table,10772259,eaidland,,,closed,Get all selected rows (row checkbox),[],[],1,"Hi!

How can I get all rows with the checkbox checked from the controller?
It looks like even though the view shows the checkbox as checked, it's not saved to the model.

 getSelectedRows = function() {
        var selected;
        selected = $scope.rowCollection.filter(function(item) {
          return item.isSelected === true;
        });
        return logger.debug('selected ' + selected);
      };

I've copied the directive ""Create your own plugin"" from the smart-table site and converted it to coffee syntax.

AngularJS v1.2.2
ST version 2.1.8
CoffeeScript

Thanks!

The view:
```
<div ng-controller=""MyController"" >
    <div class=""table-responsive"">
        <table st-table=""displayedCollection"" st-safe-src=""rowCollection"" class=""table table-striped"">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th colspan=""6""><input st-search="""" class=""form-control"" placeholder=""Search ..."" type=""text"" autofocus /></th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th></th>
                    <th st-sort=""Description"">Description</th>
                </tr>

            </thead>
            <tbody>
@*<tr st-selected-row=""row"" st-select-mode=""multiple"" ng-repeat=""row in displayedCollection"">*@
                <tr ng-repeat=""row in displayedCollection"">
                    <td cs-select=""row""></td>                    
                    <td>{{row.Description}}</td>                   
                </tr>
            </tbody>
            <tfoot>
                <tr>
                    <td colspan=""6"" class=""text-center"">
                        <div st-pagination="""" st-items-by-page=""itemsByPage"" st-displayed-pages=""4"" st-template=""pagination.custom.html""></div>
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </tfoot>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>
```
From controller:
```
$scope.itemsByPage = 5
$scope.rowCollection = []
getSelectedRows = () ->
        selected = $scope.rowCollection.filter (item) ->
          return item.isSelected == true
        logger.debug 'selected ' + selected
```
The directive:
```
angular.module(""app"")
.directive(""csSelect"", ->
        require: '^stTable'
        template: '<input type=""checkbox""/>'
        scope:
            row: '=csSelect'
            
        link: (scope, element, attrs, ctrl) ->
          element.bind('change', (evt) ->          
            scope.$apply( () ->
              ctrl.select(scope.row, 'multiple')                            
              )                                      
          )
          scope.$watch 'row.isSelected', ((newValue, oldValue)->
            if (newValue == true)
              element.parent().addClass('st-selected')              
            else 
              element.parent().removeClass('st-selected')
            return
         )
    )
```
",{},{}
