5770,IssuesEvent,2017-07-24 19:07:51+00:00,4479494,serge-sans-paille/pythran,863807,serge-sans-paille,,,closed,Mention numpy in setup.py extras_require to allow using pythran in a tox test,[],[],2,"The absence of `numpy` as a dependency is preventing us from testing `pythran` in our `tox` test. See travis build:

https://travis-ci.org/fluiddyn/fluidimage/jobs/250268847

Our tox configuration looks like this now:

```
[tox]
envlist =
    py{27,34,35,36}
    py{27,36}-pythran
    codecov

[testenv]
sitepackages = True
whitelist_externals = make
usedevelop = True
deps =
    coverage
    numpy
    matplotlib
    scipy
    psutil
    future
    pyfftw
    h5py
    ipython
    pillow
    scikit-image
    pythran: pythran
commands =
make tests_coverage
```

I propose adding an `extras_require` line in `setup` function call in pythran `setup.py` like this:
```python
 extras_require=dict(
          deps=['numpy'])
```

which should allow us to write the tox test as follows and should in practice `pip install numpy` before pythran:
```
    pythran: pythran[deps]
```
",{},{}
