6783,IssuesEvent,2016-03-09 06:47:28+00:00,8710168,django/django-contrib-comments,24574,jsma,27804,django,opened,Can't use AppConfig in INSTALLED_APPS for custom comments app,[],[],0,The import code [here](https://github.com/django/django-contrib-comments/blob/fb4d794897f492367ee40d34e8bcd9a42ef5b176/django_comments/__init__.py#L12-L31) fails if using the full dotted path to an app config in INSTALLED_APPS and COMMENTS_APP.,{},{}
6848,IssuesEvent,2017-09-28 05:45:02+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,1690881,phunterlau,47359,apache,closed,Request to update the pre-trained Inception-BN model,[],[],2,"Previously, I was trying to do fine-tuning based on [the pre-trained Inception-BN model](https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet-model-gallery/blob/master/imagenet-1k-inception-bn.md). And I encountered an issue that the fine-tuned model produced almost the same prediction scores for every test sample.

After discussing with a friend, I learned that the above issue can be fixed by properly passing the parameter `fix_gamma=False` in`mx.symbol.BatchNorm` (for Inception-BN, one needs to modify this [line](https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/example/image-classification/symbol_inception-bn.py#L18) accordingly in the symbol file).

The above issue seems to be caused by some legacy issue that the pre-trained Inception-BN model was trained by using an old version of MXNet. If so, can we expect to have an updated pre-trained Inception-BN model soon? Or at least document it for fine-tuning somewhere?

Thanks.
",{},{}
