6892,IssuesEvent,2018-07-26 04:33:18+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,2626883,szha,47359,apache,closed," ImageIter save labels as float32, which meight cause numerical precision problem","[{'id': 206159502, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwyMDYxNTk1MDI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-mxnet/labels/Bug', 'name': 'Bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': False}, {'id': 707556117, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3MDc1NTYxMTc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-mxnet/labels/Python', 'name': 'Python', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]",[],6,"https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/87068e6df91ed9b2fdbcffa4d6a83e318c002247/python/mxnet/image/image.py#L1076

This will convert the labels into the data type of float32 which has significand precision of 24 bits. When some labels are large integers (out of [-16777216,16777216] ), it will face precision limits.  An example I have met is that, when the label is 16777232, it will be changed to 167777233 after saved to imglist. It takes me a lot of time to find what's wrong.  I suggest to change float to int, or give some notice",{},{}
