6926,IssuesEvent,2018-02-26 22:43:30+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,568948,piiswrong,47359,apache,closed,A bug in an example in the python API document,"[{'id': 206159502, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-mxnet/labels/Bug', 'name': 'Bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': False}, {'id': 588394144, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-mxnet/labels/Doc', 'name': 'Doc', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],3,"This is an example found in the doc for [mxnet.autograd.Function](https://mxnet.incubator.apache.org/api/python/autograd.html#mxnet.autograd.Function).
```python
class sigmoid(Function):
    def forward(self, x):
        y = 1 / (1 + mx.nd.exp(-x))
        self.save_for_backward(y)
        return y

    def backward(self, dy):
        # backward takes as many inputs as forward's return value,
        # and returns as many NDArrays as forward's arguments.
        y, = self.saved_tensors
        return y * (1-y)
```
The `backward` method should return `dy * y * (1-y)` instead of `y * (1-y)` according to the chain rule.",{},{}
