7269,IssuesEvent,2016-05-17 18:43:15+00:00,6982635,plone/mockup,422130,davilima6,72034,plone,opened,Structure filter ui/ux,[],[],0,"In addition to #381 I propose:

**1. Initial value for Title criteria:** When user inputs something in Live Filter and then clicks the `Query` button, Plone should open the Query popover with initial `Title` criteria filled with that input. This explicits why and how the current listing is filtered already and why user doesn't get all results even if he/she clears all filters.

**2. Different buttons for Live filter and Query popover :** using `glyphicon-search` suggests users to think that button is needed to be pressed after providing input in the text field, which 1) isn't true, as the filtering happens by keystroke and 2) leads to unexpected ui behavior as a popover opens (instead of searching/filtering/querying). So I suggest:

    2.1. Update placeholder from ""Filter"" to ""Filter items"" to make label paralel to search viewlet's placeholder
    2.2. Add a button with `.glyphicon-filter` or `.glyphicon-option-horizontal` for the Advanced Query popover 
    2.3. Move `.glyphicon-search` inside and to the right of the input field, to reinforce this is a search input widget while still keeping it visually simple with only one explicit button (besides the search one would still work when js is disabled so no a11n loss)

**3. Live filter locates items _containing_ querystring**, instead of only starting with it.",{},{}
7306,IssuesEvent,2017-12-22 20:52:31+00:00,2419254,plone/plone.dexterity,70700,jaroel,72034,plone,opened,DX containers class has IContentish through DexterityContent,[],[],0,"The plone.dexterity.content.Container class gains the IContentish interface via the DexterityContent class.

```python
class Container(
        PasteBehaviourMixin, DAVCollectionMixin, BrowserDefaultMixin,
        CMFCatalogAware, CMFOrderedBTreeFolderBase, DexterityContent):
```

```python
class DexterityContent(DAVResourceMixin, PortalContent, PropertyManager,
                       Contained):
```

This *will* trigger a bunch of event handlers normally registered for content objects only for folderish (container) objects too.
",{},{}
7309,IssuesEvent,2016-04-05 10:55:08+00:00,2419254,plone/plone.dexterity,147512,do3cc,72034,plone,opened,Documentation and code ignores the fact that __getattr__ always works on acquisition unwrapped objects,[],[],0,"This causes surprising and bad behavior:
1. Create a schema
2. Add a IContextAwareDefaultFactory for one of the fields. The factory should try to access the parent
3. A view will show the information from the parent
4. Accessing the property directly in code will fail. The object is acquisition wrapped, but Python doesn't know about this magic and __getattr__ gets an unwrapped object of self. All __parent__ pointers are gone.

I wouldn't know how to fix it, unfortunately. And it should be added somewhere as a warning.",{},{}
