7967,IssuesEvent,2017-04-06 16:05:02+00:00,64985162,celery/django-celery-results,282284,psychok7,319983,celery,opened,Writing results temporarly to memory,[],[],0,"Would you consider a new feature (if there is not  a similar one already that i couldn't find) writing the celery results in a temporary cache backend (like Redis for example), and having a callable Django management command to retrieve multiple results and dump them in bulk as well into a Database (Postgres for e.g)??

