8678,IssuesEvent,2015-11-09 22:21:10+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,208705,kevbo,647025,pypa,opened,--always-copy doesn't always copy,[],[],0,"When I use --always-copy with virtualenv, I would expect that the environment it creates is completely self-contained with no dependencies outside of its own directory tree. However, that is not the case, as demonstrated in this gist: https://gist.github.com/kevbo/135b4cab839fb8adf357

There are system (well, pyenv) python directories in the path, and even though some modules have been copied, others (like traceback.py) have not.

Is --always-copy intended to create fully-isolated envs, such that I could delete the system python and still allow the env to work?",{},{}
