8809,IssuesEvent,2017-01-06 17:51:12+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,opened,Producer deadlocks when queues are full,"[{'id': 8945343, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"Steps to reproduce:

* Run a local 3-node kafka cluster, make a topic with 10 partitions and replication factor 2
* Run a producer producing messages to this topic in a `while True` loop with `max_queued_messages=5`
* Kill two of the kafka nodes
* Observe that the producer deadlocks after repeated retries

This may be related to https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/pull/633#issuecomment-269578948

**PyKafka version**: https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/commit/2cabc71b7def03e6a90dfbf767e34e6a8df54bbc
**Kafka version**: 0.9.0.1
",{},{}
8810,IssuesEvent,2015-05-07 15:36:40+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,closed,NotCoordinatorForConsumer when committing offsets to coordinator,[],[],1,"In some of my tests, I've seen the following sequence of events encountered by the `BalancedConsumer`:

* Attempt to commit offsets to broker id 11
* Get back error code 16 (`NotCoordinatorForConsumer`)
* Accordingly, rediscover the offset manager broker for this consumer group
* Discover that the offset manager is broker 11 (the one that we were talking to in the first place)

> 2015-04-30 23:13:46,987 - root - INFO - Committing offsets for 2 partitions to broker id 11
> 2015-04-30 23:13:46,990 - pykafka.cluster - INFO - Attempting to discover offset manager for consumer group 'raws-devbox'
> 2015-04-30 23:13:46,991 - pykafka.cluster - INFO - Found coordinator broker with id 11
> 2015-04-30 23:13:46,992 - root - ERROR - Error committing offsets for topic raw_pixels (error codes: [16])

At face value, this seems like an issue with kafka itself. I'll give more information here as I find it.",{},{}
8831,IssuesEvent,2015-11-05 10:19:51+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,4370917,xqliang,779641,Parsely,opened,Cantnot remove _zk_state_listener when creating BalancedProducer failed,[],[],0,"When an exception raised from [here](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L438), the `_zk_state_listener` is [added](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L239), but the `_running` flag is not set yet. So calling `stop()` is [ignored](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L251), the `_zk_state_listener` and `_zookeeper` connection [which is owned by us](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L235) are still there.

We can set `_running` to `True` before `_add_self`, but we will encounter [NoNodeError](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L268) when stop it.

Another problem, when init `BalancedConsumer` with `auto_start=True`(the default setting), and an exception raised from [here](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L438), we cannot get the  instance reference, so there is no way to do cleanups.",{},{}
