9200,IssuesEvent,2016-12-17 22:15:16+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,364113,mrcslws,1039191,numenta,opened,We should have a way of using the SparseMatrix with segments,[],[],0,"We don't currently have a way to write fast Python algorithms if the algorithms require variable number of segments per cell. Writing fast Python algorithms requires batch operations, i.e. no looping in Python. Our Connections class supports segments but it doesn't support batch operations. Our SparseMatrix supports batch operations, but we don't have a good way of using it with segments, at least not with Python code.

Possible solutions:

1. Add batch operations to Connections
2. Make it so that our Python code can use the SparseMatrix for algorithms that require segments

This issue tracks Solution 2.",{},{}
