9219,IssuesEvent,2016-05-24 09:02:27+00:00,30921526,mozilla-services/cliquet,250019,tarekziade,1066228,mozilla-services,closed,Handle Hawk signature with BATCH subrequests,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla-services/cliquet/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],3,"Currently, BATCH operations need each request to specify their authentication. This is okay for BasicAuth but can be trickier for other authentication schemes. For instance, hawk needs each request to be signed with the content of the request, which adds complexity on the client side for almost no benefit.

One way to solve this and make it easier for clients would be to allow the specification of credentials in the BATCH request headers, and do not need to specify it during the sub-requests.",{},{}
