9411,IssuesEvent,2017-03-16 20:24:31+00:00,4802269,dnanexus/dx-toolkit,24255381,kpjensen,1161297,dnanexus,closed,Download all inputs regression due to PTFM-18767,[],[],1,"Changes from [PTFM-18767](https://github.com/dnanexus/dx-toolkit/blob/90902a101935b30f53659a033e5d5c6ddd976505/src/python/dxpy/bindings/download_all_inputs.py#L189-L194) results in usage of `dxpy.download_all_inputs(parallel=True)` to hang and slowly eat available memory.

`max_threads` is still an optional parameter that [is not set to a default value](https://github.com/dnanexus/dx-toolkit/commit/90902a101935b30f53659a033e5d5c6ddd976505#diff-d9c1c9ff7742a1569532d53081ead50cL182) before being used in [`min()`](https://github.com/dnanexus/dx-toolkit/commit/90902a101935b30f53659a033e5d5c6ddd976505#diff-d9c1c9ff7742a1569532d53081ead50cR112) to find the number of parallel workers. As a result Number of workers is always [set to None](https://github.com/dnanexus/dx-toolkit/blob/90902a101935b30f53659a033e5d5c6ddd976505/src/python/dxpy/bindings/download_all_inputs.py#L63).

Probably add the default value for `max_threads` back. Perhaps handle `max_workers=0` for ThreadPoolExecutor constructor?",{},{}
9448,IssuesEvent,2017-05-06 08:34:34+00:00,8410895,zopefoundation/AccessControl,483109,hannosch,1163184,zopefoundation,closed,Adjust to newer Record release,[],"[{'login': 'hannosch', 'id': 483109, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/483109?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/hannosch', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hannosch/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"`AccessControl.SimpleObjectPolicies` includes:
```
Record.Record.__allow_access_to_unprotected_subobjects__ = 1
```

The upcoming Record 3.3 release does this in its own code. Once a new Record release is done, AccessControl can drop this line.

At that point AccessControl doesn't need to depend on Record at all anymore, and it can be removed from `setup.py`.",{},{}
