>>> dt.fread(""NaN\n2"")
                C0
---  -------------
 0    0           
 1   -2.68156e+154

[2 rows x 1 column]
```
It appears that the presence of NaN causes multiple re-reads, and in the end it doesn't do it correctly anyways... The bug appears very rare, the following conditions are necessary:
* The header row is absent
* ""NaN"" literal is in the first row
* the remaining rows contain integers (not floats)",{},{}
