10424,IssuesEvent,2017-08-03 06:27:04+00:00,38744670,zalando/patroni,3407345,CyberDem0n,1564818,zalando,closed,Alternative to backup-config files,"[{'id': 233785761, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zalando/patroni/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 233785762, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zalando/patroni/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}]",[],7,"I wanted to suggest an atlernative to the current backup config files functionality on that branch.

We could support a conf.d directory, which would be outside PGDATA, and thus not wiped out by restores.

I believe this is a much better route than backing up and restoring conf files:
1. we don't have to touch those files, so they could be maintained by a CMF
2. doesn't involve a bunch of copying files
3. makes it easier to extend functionality by simply dropping files in the conf.d directory

... in fact, I plan to implement conf.d support anyway, so why not just go that way?

If there's some reason why you also need pg.conf backup, then can we please make it an _optional_ feature?  For container-based deployments, it makes no sense to be ""backing up"" pg.conf etc.
",{},{}
