10613,IssuesEvent,2018-06-13 18:17:31+00:00,83072729,CartoDB/cartoframes,12551177,michellemho,1799254,CartoDB,opened,Discrepancy between CARTO data and Exported Data,[],"[{'login': 'andy-esch', 'id': 1041056, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDEwNTY=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1041056?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/andy-esch', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-esch/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"This is not a problem that is unique to CARTOframes, so if there's another repo I should put this in, please let me know!

**Problem**: Exported data from CARTO does not match data as it appears in CARTO. There appear to be some ""hidden"" rows in CARTO... why?

Steps to reproduce:

1. Go to https://team.carto.com/u/michellemho-carto/dataset/michellemho-carto.nyc_blockgroups_commuters. Verify that shapes that CARTO is showing the islands south of Brooklyn and Queens, and everything is shoreline clipped. Everything looks as expected.

<img width=""1249"" alt=""screen shot 2018-06-13 at 1 58 28 pm"" src=""https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12551177/41369363-ac90f71e-6f12-11e8-8f02-ef77578897ff.png"">

2. Download GeoJSON (or Shapefile)
<img width=""1047"" alt=""screen shot 2018-06-13 at 1 58 41 pm"" src=""https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12551177/41369447-dc4fd812-6f12-11e8-9398-ee242d855288.png"">

3. Upload GeoJSON to new map
![screen shot 2018-06-13 at 1 59 00 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12551177/41369458-e7be8748-6f12-11e8-8b86-8e929aea0a32.png)

4. See that extra areas are now suddenly visible (for example, polygon below State Island that is water) Where did they come from?

![screen shot 2018-06-13 at 2 00 15 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12551177/41369888-2e3b7252-6f14-11e8-83d5-822ba4045b55.png)

I did some investigating, and found that in the original dataset, these ""extra"" polygons actually exist. They are just not appearing when I create maps this original dataset. What is going on? Why are they hidden?",{},{}
