10785,IssuesEvent,2016-11-03 14:34:55+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,398875,neubig,2374376,clab,closed,Inconsistent invalid argument exceptions,"[{'id': 439660182, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/clab/dynet/labels/need%20more%20info', 'name': 'need more info', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]",[],4,"I'm using the Python bindings and I [use](https://github.com/danielhers/ucca/blob/dynet/parsing/classifiers/nn/feedforward.py#L45) `reshape` to change a batch of embeddings into one long vector.
The same code sometimes works fine and sometimes fails with the [error](https://travis-ci.org/danielhers/ucca/jobs/172277222) `Bad arguments to Reshape: {3200}, {10X32}`.
In the same network I [use](https://github.com/danielhers/ucca/blob/dynet/parsing/classifiers/nn/feedforward.py#L59) matrix multiplication, and this also sometimes fails the [error](https://travis-ci.org/danielhers/ucca/jobs/172277231) `Mismatched input dimensions in MatrixMultiply: [{200} {200}]`.
