10890,IssuesEvent,2017-10-27 09:16:49+00:00,58705171,opencobra/memote,4471699,jjkoehorst,2708410,opencobra,opened,Test gitlab runner,[],[],0,"I have made a simple initial attempt to get Memote running on gitlab.

* Modifications to the docker image was needed 

I disabled:

#ENTRYPOINT [""memote""]
#CMD [""-h""]

And pushed it to ""jjkoehorst/memote"" at docker hub

The second issue is as mentioned on gitter:

Memote looks if it is inside a git repo and if so it looks like it tries to access the history. The default of gitlab is that it takes only the HEAD state to prevent entire changes to be pushed for testing as in theory (for product development) you would not need this. 

Thus I copy the model.xml to a root folder ""/"" and then it seems to ""run"" the validations and generate a JSON file. 

Have to look into the reporting mechanism or that the standard output that is printed to the console is sufficient. As I have however not found a way to push the results back to the repo (and possibly create an infinite loop). 

The repo job run results are here: https://gitlab.com/wurssb/memote-demo/-/jobs/37923063 

On the right you can see the within git run and the root run under ""/"". It also generates an exit code 1 which I am looking into now
",{},{}
