11065,IssuesEvent,2017-10-24 17:09:33+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,247555,tswast,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,closed,Add startIndex to bigquery.table.Table.fetch_data,"[{'id': 82126549, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/labels/api:%20bigquery', 'name': 'api: bigquery', 'color': 'cd7f32', 'default': False}, {'id': 544604235, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/labels/status:%20acknowledged', 'name': 'status: acknowledged', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}, {'id': 77438582, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/labels/type:%20enhancement', 'name': 'type: enhancement', 'color': '8bc34a', 'default': False}]",[],2,"The API describes a `startIndex` parameter for the [""Tabledata: list"" endpoint](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/tabledata/list). But the implementation [doesn't include this parameter](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/blob/master/bigquery/google/cloud/bigquery/table.py#L645). An example of a class does implement a `startIndex` parameter is [bigquery.query.Query](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/blob/master/bigquery/google/cloud/bigquery/query.py#L367) as described in the [""Jobs: getQueryResults"" endpoint](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/jobs/getQueryResults).

I tried editing the code to submit a PR, but I'm not familiar with testing this kind of Python package locally (`pip install -e .` didn't install the packages from their local copy as I expected). In lieu of a PR I can share this patched class `TableWithStartIndex` that works for my use case:

```python
from google.cloud.bigquery.table import Table, _item_to_row, _rows_page_start
from google.cloud.iterator import HTTPIterator
class TableWithStartIndex(Table):
    def fetch_data_with_start_index(self, max_results=None, page_token=None, client=None, start_index=None):
        client = self._require_client(client)
        path = '%s/data' % (self.path,)
        extra_params = {}
        if start_index is not None:
            extra_params['startIndex'] = start_index
        iterator = HTTPIterator(client=client, path=path,
                                item_to_value=_item_to_row, items_key='rows',
                                page_token=page_token, max_results=max_results,
                                page_start=_rows_page_start,
                                extra_params=extra_params)
        iterator.schema = self._schema
        # Over-ride the key used to retrieve the next page token.
        iterator._NEXT_TOKEN = 'pageToken'
        return iterator
```

I added three small chunks: the `start_index=None` argument, this block:

```python
        extra_params = {}
        if start_index is not None:
            extra_params['startIndex'] = start_index
```

And the bit that passes the `extra_params` to the `HTTPIterator`: `extra_params=extra_params`.",{},{}
