11421,IssuesEvent,2016-12-23 01:57:52+00:00,7137821,cloudtools/troposphere,6900888,jonstacks,3028687,cloudtools,opened,[Enhancement] Return Values and Equality for Objects,[],[],0,"Hi,

Firstly, I wanted to say thanks for a great library that helps me generate my cloud formation templates much easier than by hand. I've been trying to write some tests for my code, but I often run into an issue when checking for equality. Here is an example:

<img width=""313"" alt=""screen shot 2016-12-22 at 7 32 46 pm"" src=""https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6900888/21445374/d1a3878e-c87d-11e6-9012-b3f29f9e8db1.png"">

I was wondering if it would be possible to implement equality for a lot of these objects. I found the `to_json` method on the `Template` class and have just been doing this for now in my tests


```python
def equal(x, y):
    kwargs = {'cls': awsencode, 'indent': 4, 'sort_keys': True, 'separators': (',', ': ')}
    return json.dumps(x, **kwargs) == json.dumps(y, **kwargs)
```

Also, I was wondering about adding properties to the objects for their return values. I often find myself doing the following:

```python
elb = elasticloadbalancing.LoadBalancer(""MyLoadbalancer"")
# ...
GetAtt(elb, ""CanonicalHostedZoneName"")  # For use as an output or in a DNS entry or whatever...
```

I have monkey patched that class so that I can do on all my elbs:

<img width=""388"" alt=""screen shot 2016-12-22 at 7 49 04 pm"" src=""https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6900888/21445526/c57c8f6c-c87f-11e6-983c-527f4e348c9a.png"">

This saves me the trouble of importing GetAtt, I get some nice tab completion, and I think it makes my code look a little cleaner. Would anyone else find functionality like this useful or am I alone in this? If so, I'd be more than willing to contribute.


Thanks,",{},{}
