    installer_provider)
  File ""c:\python27\lib\site-packages\pex\bin\pex.py"", line 361, in _resolve_and_link_interpreter
    egg = EggPackage(os.path.realpath(target_link))
  File ""c:\python27\lib\site-packages\pex\package.py"", line 150, in __init__
    raise self.InvalidPackage('Not an egg: %s' % filename)
pex.package.InvalidPackage: Not an egg: wheel
```

I fixed this by uninstalling  wheel, then installing the version pex wants.

```
PS C:\Users\Administrator\code\core> pip uninstall wheel
Uninstalling wheel-0.29.0:
Proceed (y/n)? y
  Successfully uninstalled wheel-0.29.0
PS C:\Users\Administrator\code\core> pip install wheel==0.25
