11527,IssuesEvent,2018-02-02 10:42:37+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,805730,torholm,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Dependencies not added to package.json for node_modules with yarn as package manager,[],[],0,"When using yarn as package manager for a `node_module` target, the specified `dependencies` are not added to `package.json` like they are when using `npm`.

## Example:

foo/BUILD
```

node_remote_module(
  name='jquery',
  version='3.3.1',
)

node_module(
  name='example',
  sources=globs('package.json', 'yarn.lock'),
  package_manager='yarn',
)
```

foo/package.json
```json
{}
```

foo/yarn.lock
```
```

When running `./pants compile foo:example`, the contents of package.json is not changed:

.pants.d/resolve/node/current/foo.example/current/package.json`
```
{}
```

However, if you comment out `package_manager=""yarn""`, package.json will be populated:
```json
{
  ""version"": ""0.0.0"",
  ""name"": ""example"",
  ""dependencies"": {
    ""jquery"": ""3.3.1""
  }
}
```",{},{}
11552,IssuesEvent,2018-02-02 18:25:22+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,7378,baroquebobcat,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,"[missing-deps-suggest] doesn't understand scopes, which can be confusing",[],[],0,"[missing-deps-suggest] doesn't understand scopes. This can cause confusion because if a dependency is marked with a scope other than compile, it'll be suggested even though it's already in the dependency list. I think that makes it less trustworthy.

An example.
```
java_library(name='a',
 sources=['AClassDependingOnB.java'],
  dependencies=['b']
)

java_library(name='b',
  sources=['B.java'],
  scope='runtime',
)
```

Assuming that `AClassDependingOnB` imports `B`, then when A is compiled, missing-deps-suggest will suggest adding `:b` as a dependency, but it already is one.",{},{}
11561,IssuesEvent,2015-03-27 14:01:37+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,119728,ericzundel,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Build fails after pants upgrade:  'jmake: .../global_depfile (No such file or directory)',[],[],0,"In an upgrade to pants from a version earlier than 0.0.30 to a later version, your build may fail with:

```
jmake: /Users/pantsuser/src/.pants.d/compile/jvm/apt/jmake-depfiles/global_depfile (No such file or directory)
```

To work around this issue, just run

```
./pants clean-all
```

This file is new in this version of pants and Pants gets confused because the build cache is populated but this file is missing.",{},{}
11567,IssuesEvent,2018-06-01 21:35:05+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Nailgun processes that fail to be spawned don't explain why,"[{'id': 416477283, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0MTY0NzcyODM=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/UX', 'name': 'UX', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 407699339, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0MDc2OTkzMzk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/jvm', 'name': 'jvm', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'illicitonion', 'id': 1131704, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjExMzE3MDQ=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1131704?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/illicitonion', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/illicitonion/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"If a nailgun process fails to start, the message that's presented is 

