```

##### Steps to reproduce
```
1. Start exabgp with the above configuration, downstream peer does not send any routes upstream.
2. Wait a few days.
3. One of the exabgp nodes will show a BGP connection reset and then hit 100% cpu.
```

##### Importance
```
Yes, is affecting us in a production environment, but despite using 100% CPU exabgp continues to work. It simply spins the CPU.
```

##### External Script
check_dns.sh
```
#!/usr/bin/env bash
STATE=""down""
while true; do
  dig +time=3 +tries=4 $2 @$1 +short | grep $3 >/dev/null 2>&1
  if [[ $? == 0 ]]; then
    if [[ ""$STATE"" != ""up"" ]]; then
      echo ""announce watchdog dns-$4""
      STATE=""up""
    fi
  else
    if [[ ""$STATE"" != ""down"" ]]; then
      echo ""withdraw watchdog dns-$4""
      STATE=""down""
    fi
  fi
  sleep 2
done
```

