12209,IssuesEvent,2015-01-14 16:13:40+00:00,12407457,Exa-Networks/exabgp,10435042,tim-preston,5339170,Exa-Networks,opened,When using multiple config files second and subsequent files clone sessions from the first,[],[],0,"I seem to have a problem when running multiple config files ina single ExaBGP instance. What is hapening is that the first config file on the command line is running as expected, but sessions in the second and subsequent config files seem to be cloning the details from the first config. So if I have four config files with the 100 sesions each I see the first 100 sessions configured in the first config file work fine, but the others seem to be trying to re-use the sessins details from the first config file. N.B. This config is a for a BGP load gnerator so all the sesions are to the same destination but with different local settings. I'm happy to provide more data in private if required.

I can work around this by not splitting the config file and just loading the single file. As I'm running about 400 emulated peers from a single server this does give me a significant performance hit over running with four config files.

The simplest case I can show to reproduce this using two config files follows.

Command line
```
~/exabgp/exabgp-3.4.7/sbin/exabgp -d test.exa-195.66.224.1 test.exa-195.66.224.2
```

Config files

test.exa-195.66.224.1
