12486,IssuesEvent,2015-03-12 15:40:38+00:00,13512018,python-diamond/Diamond,65675,josegonzalez,5668086,python-diamond,closed,Debian package does not create group for diamond user,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-diamond/Diamond/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],2,"I am not sure if this is intended behavior, but currently creating a debian package and installing creates a 'diamond' user but does not explicitly place that user into a group. I would expect that a group 'diamond' would also be created. I have not looked at either the RHEL/gentoo packaging to see if this is the same behavior. Is not having an explicit group created expected?

Thanks!",{},{}
12540,IssuesEvent,2015-08-20 02:19:34+00:00,4744355,soft-matter/trackpy,2279598,danielballan,5857177,soft-matter,opened,Are we ready to tag v0.3.0rc1?,[],[],0,"There are a few outstanding items on the v0.3 milestone, but they all relate to build issues (conda), docs, and trackpy-examples. How do we feel about a release candidate this weekend, aiming to tag the final v0.3.0 by mid-September?

I'm not forgetting the discussion around a minor tweak to logging, which could sneak in before the final v0.3.0 or go into v0.3.1. I also want to look at `GOOD_ENOUGH_THRESH` in light @caspervdw's fix to the test suite, but I think that could wait for v0.3.1 as well.

I am hopeful that trackpy will follow the general trend in the scientific Python community toward more frequent minor releases. Conda and versioneer make this less time-consuming than it used to be.

Thoughts?",{},{}
