12703,IssuesEvent,2015-06-17 17:59:06+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,7416231,smothiki,6117407,deis,closed,Failure to create a container leaves others created,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/scheduler', 'name': 'scheduler', 'color': 'fad8c7'}]",[],15,"If `deis scale cmd=5` creates 4 containers but fails on the 5th, it raises an exception and leaves 4 containers in the ""created"" state, not running. The code in question is here: https://github.com/deis/deis/blob/master/controller/api/models.py#L272-L292

It would be more intuitive and useful behavior if instead Deis made a ""best effort"" to start whichever containers it was able to create. In this particular case we used `deis limits:set -c cmd=1024` to ensure some containers wouldn't be created due to resource limitations, then scaled up, and were left with this:
```console
$ deis info
=== zigzag-drumroll Application
{
  ""updated"": ""2015-04-30T22:05:12UTC"", 
  ""uuid"": ""0c0dd591-5d9c-45c4-914d-52d703886cb3"", 
  ""created"": ""2015-04-30T21:53:21UTC"", 
  ""url"": ""zigzag-drumroll.local5.deisapp.com"", 
  ""owner"": ""test"", 
  ""id"": ""zigzag-drumroll"", 
  ""structure"": {
    ""cmd"": 1
  }
}

=== zigzag-drumroll Processes

--- cmd: 
cmd.1 created (v3)
cmd.2 created (v3)
cmd.3 created (v3)
cmd.4 created (v3)
cmd.5 destroyed (v3)
```",{},{}
