",{},{}
12718,IssuesEvent,2018-08-28 19:06:25+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,1300022,sirosen,6120321,globus,closed,Work out a design for fetching release notes,"[{'id': 338347011, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMzgzNDcwMTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'sirosen', 'id': 1300022, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjEzMDAwMjI=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1300022?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/sirosen', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sirosen/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"We need a way of fetching release notes for all of the releases between the current and upcoming revisions if we want `globus update` to show what's changing.

I've thought about a few ways of doing this, and they all have problems.

Basically, I see 5 sensible places for us to put changelog data for this feature:
- In pypi.org , by adding a changelog to the `long_description` field and ensuring that we can parse it
- In downloads.globus.org , where it can be whatever format is convenient (multiple txt files, single JSON file, etc), e.g. `downloads.globus.org/cli/changelog.json`
- In the CLI repo's `master` branch, where it should probably be a single file (probably JSON to ease parsing)
- docs.globus.org , potentially as a JSON or flat text file alongside `docs.globus.org/cli/reference/changelog`
- In GitHub Releases descriptions, which can be fetched via tag after versions are pulled from pypi data

The options wherein we need the data to be non-json but parseable or recognizable in some way are bound to be fragile. That basically rules out pypi , but not the other options.

I also feel nervous about relying on `https://github.com/globus/globus-cli/raw/master/changelog.json` or somesuch -- if we move the repo or change things around in the future, this seems pretty limiting.
It's unlikely that we'll change hosting or anything in the foreseeable future, but I'd like not to sow problems for us into the future. This could also be a problem for GitHub Releases. I'd be more comfortable with Releases, a dedicated feature for this purpose, than a flat file of our own design, which we might move or remove (on purpose or by accident).

docs.globus.org and downloads.globus.org are under our control, and the only downside I can see is
- for docs.globus.org, you need your PR to merge for new docs to be uploaded
- for downloads.globus.org, we'd need to distribute credentials to CLI devs for uploading a new changelog to S3

Both seem fine to me -- and better than trying to build on top of pypi -- and then I guess it's a question of what @jaswilli, @shifflett-globus, and @aaschaer prefer?
I'd consider docs.globus.org, downloads.globus.org, and GitHub Releases to all be in the running.
Or is there some other place we could put our changelog to keep it parseable which I'm missing?",{},{}
