12941,IssuesEvent,2018-01-24 20:41:31+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,closed,conda activate does not change CONDA_SUBDIR,[],[],5,"I am running Anaconda on Windows 64 bits (conda version: 4.3.30). I need to get a 32 bits python environment for compatibility with 32 bits dlls. I followed suggestions in [this closed issue](https://github.com/conda/conda/issues/1744) and ran the following:
```
conda activate root
conda info
set CONDA_SUBDIR=win-32
conda create -n newenv_win32
conda activate new_env_win32
conda info
conda activate root
conda info
```

The platform returned by the `conda info` calls was win-64, then win-32, then win-32. 

Is this intended ? Am I supposed to change CONDA_SUBDIR manually, or are there better ways to create 32 bits environments ?",{},{}
