13262,IssuesEvent,2017-06-27 17:35:56+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,13154635,EricABC,6844498,Azure,opened,Can no longer create container registry due to unavailable apiVersion,[],[],0,"### Description
**Outline the issue here:**

```az acr create -n ... -g ... --sku Managed_Standard``` fails since the new version (which adds delete capabilities) elevated the apiVersion for registries to 2017-06-01-preview.  ```az provider show -n Microsoft.ContainerRegistry``` shows only 2017-03-01.  My goal was to recreate with a managed storage SKU so I could use delete.  To the best of my knowledge it isn't related to my azure subscription so I filed here.  I already tried re-registering ContainerRegistry under subscriptions, in case that was necessary.  The error code is NoRegisteredProviderFound.  The update seems to be a week ago here https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/commit/855f1233a4211c99cb7708833b5c85d5a47b36bf


---

### Environment summary

Newest CLI, includes acr 2.0.7

**Install Method:** How did you install the CLI? (e.g. pip, interactive script, apt-get, Docker, MSI, nightly)  
Answer here: Both MSI and BashUW

**CLI Version:** What version of the CLI and modules are installed? (Use `az --version`)  
Answer here: 2.0.9 (acr 2.0.7)

**OS Version:** What OS and version are you using?  
Answer here: win10

**Shell Type:** What shell are you using? (e.g. bash, cmd.exe, Bash on Windows)  
Answer here: PS/Bash

",{},{}
13266,IssuesEvent,2017-05-04 22:08:34+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,6014209,yugangw-msft,6844498,Azure,closed,auth: cache adal token cache in memory,"[{'id': 418938653, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Auth', 'name': 'Auth', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],0,"The goal is to use a single copy of token cache across the same process, rather dump it after getting a token. Building up a token cache is non trivial involving reading and writing the ~/.azure/accesstoken.json. For some commands which involves 1000+ rest call, like datalake, the perf hit is not trivial.",{},{}
