13275,IssuesEvent,2017-02-15 19:56:05+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,8792554,jtuliani,6844498,Azure,opened,[DNS] Null fields output in JSON when adding DNS record,[],[],0,"Consider:

C:\Users\jonatul>az network dns record a add -g rg1 -z jt-test.com --record-set-name cli2 --ipv4-address 1.2.3.8
{
  ""aaaaRecords"": null,
  ""arecords"": [
    {
      ""ipv4Address"": ""1.2.3.5""
    },
    {
      ""ipv4Address"": ""1.2.3.6""
    },
    {
      ""ipv4Address"": ""1.2.3.8""
    }
  ],
  ""cnameRecord"": null,
  ""etag"": ""969c645b-d5d5-4f28-86ec-fa1f98a147b0"",
  ""id"": ""/subscriptions/a385a691-bd93-41b0-8084-8213ebc5bff7/resourceGroups/rg1/providers/Microsoft.Network/dnszones/jt-test.com/A/cli2"",
  ""metadata"": null,
  ""mxRecords"": null,
  ""name"": ""cli2"",
  ""nsRecords"": null,
  ""ptrRecords"": null,
  ""resourceGroup"": ""rg1"",
  ""soaRecord"": null,
  ""srvRecords"": null,
  ""ttl"": 3600,
  ""txtRecords"": null,
  ""type"": ""Microsoft.Network/dnszones/A""
}

This is an A record, hence only the 'aRecords' property is relevant.  The properties for other record types (shown as 'null' above) were not sent over the wire by the REST API. They should not appear in the output.

Please keep the '""metadata"": null' however, that is fine as is and should be in the output.
",{},{}
