13421,IssuesEvent,2017-07-30 02:43:07+00:00,72874378,prestodb/presto-python-client,2192913,highker,6882181,prestodb,opened,Retry fails with 503,[],[],0,Retry currently lives at http.`post`/`get`/`delete` level. 503 error is handled in `process()`. Raise a 503 error in `process()` is not going to invoke retry. This could also be a problem with authentication retry. Need to think about how to abstract retry in a more generic way. ,{},{}
