14093,IssuesEvent,2018-03-16 02:29:46+00:00,24375248,blockstack/blockstack-core,17980605,haiki,8165984,blockstack,opened,How exactly Virtualchain and consensus hash  works?,[],[],0,"After days learning, I am totally confused by the mechnism of  virtualchain and  consensus rules . 
so I want to know how virtualchain store blocks which parses transactions from blockchain, What kind of database is used? how to anthenticate transactions which are valid or not by consensus hash  ?  as some transactions have consensus hash but others not . 
and how virtual chain block's format looks like ? Are the blocks of virtualchain and blockchain corresponding to one by one? if so,once  blcokchain's block wihtout operation ,here will be many stale virtualchain block?
May be here are enough doc for my questions but I am not understand them . so I'm looking forward to yours reply ! thanks~",{},{}
14095,IssuesEvent,2017-06-29 17:54:39+00:00,24375248,blockstack/blockstack-core,597182,larrysalibra,8165984,blockstack,closed,Trouble with storage authorization,"[{'id': 534458999, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/blockstack/blockstack-core/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': True}]",[],1,"I **was** having trouble figuring out why I'm not authorized to create and write to datastores. I wrote up this issue ticket to seek help from @jcnelson.

I already figured out the cause of this problem and will share it in a comment. I didn't want to waste the time I spent writing this up in case it's useful for others in the future. 
---
