', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RonnyPfannschmidt/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RonnyPfannschmidt/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RonnyPfannschmidt/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RonnyPfannschmidt/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'tgoodlet', 'id': 291685, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/291685?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/tgoodlet', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tgoodlet/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'nicoddemus', 'id': 1085180, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1085180?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nicoddemus', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicoddemus/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"As per pytest-dev/pytest#1821 @RonnyPfannschmidt has mentioned it's worth discussing if `pluggy.PluginManager` should have a *strict* mode where every single plugin which is loaded is verified against a spec instead of only performing this validation each time `PluginManager.check_pending()` is called.

In `pytest` `check_pending()` is only done once just prior to the `pytest_cmdline_main(config=config)` call meaning unverified hooks can be loaded any time afterwards.

This issue is to open discussion and brainstorming.",{},{}
14369,IssuesEvent,2017-05-10 14:58:35+00:00,33952074,pytest-dev/pytest-html,4374581,liiight,8897583,pytest-dev,opened,Add ability to create custom assets,[],[],0,"If such ability already exist and I missed it, I apologize.
I have some api calls using `requests` module. I want to add a CURL format of the request when the test fails.
I use the `metadata` plugin to inject my string:
```python
req = e.response.request
metadata['curl'] = request_to_curl(req)
```
Then I'm overriding the table as such:
```python
@pytest.mark.hookwrapper
def pytest_runtest_makereport(item, call):
    pytest_html = item.config.pluginmanager.getplugin('html')
    outcome = yield
    report = outcome.get_result()
    extra = getattr(report, 'extra', [])
    if report.when == 'call':
        xfail = hasattr(report, 'wasxfail')
        if (report.skipped and xfail) or (report.failed and not xfail):
            # only add curl on failure
            if item.config._metadata.get('curl'):
                report.curl = pytest_html.extras.text(item.config._metadata.get('curl'))
        report.extra = extra


@pytest.mark.optionalhook
def pytest_html_results_table_header(cells):
    cells.insert(3, html.th('CURL'))
    cells.pop()


@pytest.mark.optionalhook
def pytest_html_results_table_row(report, cells):
    cells.insert(3, html.td(report.curl, class_='col-links'))
    cells.pop()
```
This return the unprepared asset, which I would like to run using [create_asset](https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-html/blob/master/pytest_html/plugin.py#L137).
Obviously I can duplicate its code, but if there was a way to do this natively, it would be great.
",{},{}
14374,IssuesEvent,2017-12-16 02:42:51+00:00,41756998,pytest-dev/pytest-xdist,1697486,DanaGoyette,8897583,pytest-dev,opened,dist=loadscope scheduling hangs on test class with only one test,[],[],0,"With pytest 3.2.3, when I tried using --dist=loadscope with two ssh nodes, the test framework simply hung without even trying to run any tests.  The same environment works fine with the other schedulers.

Part of the traceback (seems exactly the same as #230 ):
        while not self.session_finished:
>           self.loop_once()

The hang seems to occur when running a test class that has only one test function.
I eventually tracked down a simple change that seems to fix it: on the following line, expect only one item, not two:

https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-xdist/blob/master/xdist/remote.py#L62

I can't tell what the change might break, though.",{},{}
