14563,IssuesEvent,2017-08-25 13:08:30+00:00,26784827,dotnet/core,18699147,johanskoldekrans,9141961,dotnet,opened,Asp-controller and asp-action attributes order,[],[],0,"If a make an a-tag in html on the view and put asp-* tags (for example asp-controller, asp-action and asp-route) after a @(some code)-section and a class-attribute it breaks the interpretation of the asp-* attributes.

Below example doesnt pick up the route-id:
`
<a asp-controller=""Some"" asp-action=""Something"" class=""@(x == y ? ""something"" : """")"" asp-route-id=""1"">Click me</a>
`
if I put all after nothing happens (no href is generated):
`
<a class=""@(x == y ? ""something"" : """")"" asp-controller=""Some"" asp-action=""Something"" asp-route-id=""1"">Click me</a>
`
Is this behaviour as design?

VS 2017 15.3.2
.NETCore 2.1.0-preview1-26778
.EFCore 2.1.0-preview1-26778
Windows 10 Insider (slow ring)
