14879,IssuesEvent,2017-08-22 19:32:49+00:00,42750248,watson-developer-cloud/python-sdk,534589,ry0ohki,10017763,watson-developer-cloud,opened,"The Python Watson SDK attempts its own media type detection when the user provides a file, and it should not",[],[],0,"If a user provides a file, but doesn't specify the media type, when adding a document to Discovery using the Python Watson SDK, then Python attempts to auto-detect the media type. However, Discovery itself is capable of determining the media type, and arguably, it has a robust algorithm to do so. As such, the Python SDK should not attempt to do this on its own. Instead, it should default the media type to application/octet-stream which ensures that Discovery's media type detection will be used.",{},{}
