15283,IssuesEvent,2017-02-16 01:04:03+00:00,30895522,pvlib/pvlib-python,4383303,wholmgren,11037261,pvlib,opened,fix or silence expected numpy RuntimeWarnings,"[{'id': 177800479, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pvlib/pvlib-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],0,"A handful of pvlib functions generate numpy RuntimeWarnings for typical inputs. We should tweak the pvlib code or wrap specific lines with [np.errstate](https://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy-1.12.0/reference/generated/numpy.errstate.html) context managers. Pandas used to silence numpy RuntimeWarnings, but they wisely changed that in 0.18 or 0.19.

These functions and linked lines need work:

- [ ] [perez](https://github.com/pvlib/pvlib-python/blob/master/pvlib/irradiance.py#L1002-L1009)
- [ ] [physicaliam](https://github.com/pvlib/pvlib-python/blob/master/pvlib/pvsystem.py#L818-L836)
- [ ] [sapm](https://github.com/pvlib/pvlib-python/blob/master/pvlib/pvsystem.py#L1302-L1310)
- [ ] [i_from_v](https://github.com/pvlib/pvlib-python/blob/master/pvlib/pvsystem.py#L1943)

I'm probably missing a few, so I'll add to this as we discover more.",{},{}
