[miny1.gz](https://github.com/angr/angr/files/2251198/miny1.gz)

```
import angr
prj = angr.Project('miny1', load_options={'auto_load_libs':False})
cfg = prj.analyses.CFGAccurate()
cg = cfg.functions.callgraph
node_addrs = [addr for addr in cg.nodes]
addr = node_addrs[0]
print 'addr:', hex(addr)
func = cfg.functions.function(addr)
print func.name
```

The output I get from running the above program is below:
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""./cause_bug.py"", line 10, in <module>
    print func.name
AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'name'
```
Binary `miny1` was compiled using the following commands

```
git clone https://github.com/spacecamper/miny.git
cd miny
sudo apt-get install freeglut3 freeglut3-dev
make
```
I modified the Makefile of miny to use gcc compiler optimization level1 and to change the file name of the generated binary from `miny` to `miny1`.",{},{}
