15850,IssuesEvent,2018-02-20 05:45:13+00:00,38554391,ValvePython/steam,20358177,tmart2322,12702757,ValvePython,closed,Generating Codes with Shared Secret,[],[],1,"I am having an issue generating the correct Steam Guard codes when trying to login in. I am using the below code, but it seems as though the generated codes are different than that on the authenticator I am using (I am using Steam Desktop Authenticator for reference). I made sure I am using the correct shared secret based on the steam account. The error this method is login function is throwing is TwoFactorCodeRequired (even though I supply it below). I tried using the code SteamDektopAuthenticator gives and it is correct.  Any further ideas as to why the generated code is different?

```
