16825,IssuesEvent,2018-06-21 22:15:53+00:00,55101236,googleapis/artman,26395,warhammerkid,16785467,googleapis,opened,proto files not included in ruby gem,[],[],0,"Similar to to googleapis/artman#351, it would be helpful if the googleapis-common-protos-types ruby gem included the proto files in addition to the code generated ruby definitions. As it is currently, compiling proto files using the `google.api.http` option requires vendoring a copy of the googleapis/googleapis repo into the project.

From a usage perspective I was envisioning being able to do something like the following:

```ruby
grpc_tools_spec = Gem::Specification.find_by_name('grpc-tools')
googleapis_spec = Gem::Specification.find_by_name('googleapis-common-protos-types')
bin_path = File.join(grpc_tools_spec.bin_dir, 'grpc_tools_ruby_protoc')
exec(bin_path,
  ""-I."",
  ""-I#{File.join(googleapis_spec.gem_dir, 'proto')}"",
