17024,IssuesEvent,2018-04-16 08:47:11+00:00,65545148,bigchaindb/bigchaindb-driver,1210951,ttmc,17097586,bigchaindb,opened,Problem: Some users unable to upgrade to the latest version,"[{'id': 488220399, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/bigchaindb/bigchaindb-driver/labels/docs', 'name': 'docs', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}]",[],0,"The latest version of the Python driver, 0.5.0a1, is a ""pre-release"" (or at least that's what I heard; I couldn't find any indication of this fact on PyPI, i.e. at https://pypi.python.org/pypi/bigchaindb-driver ). That means that just doing:
```bash
$ pip install -U bigchaindb_driver
```

will not upgrade them to 0.5.0a1, because it's not a ""release"", it's a pre-release. They must do:
```bash
$ pip install bigchaindb_driver==0.5.0a1
```

### To Do

- Figure out how to get PyPI to indicate that it's a pre-release.
- Update the docs (including those on PyPI) on how to install / upgrade the driver, to account for the case when the latest version is a pre-release.
",{},{}
