17284,IssuesEvent,2018-03-22 23:20:28+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,opened,Delay handling of ctrl+c during error handling,"[{'id': 272789317, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/area:%20error%20handling', 'name': 'area: error handling', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}]",[],0,"In the docstring for `certbot.error_handler.ErrorHandler` we say:

> Signals received while the registered functions are executing are deferred until they finish.

People have told me this isn't the case with `SIGINT` from ctrl+c though. This is probably one of the most common signals we'll get so we should try and handle this properly. It doesn't look like we're overriding the signal handler for `SIGINT` but maybe we should, at least when running the registered functions.",{},{}
