17480,IssuesEvent,2018-05-12 12:56:58+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,closed,Remove the DummyTransport,[],"[{'login': 'jomuel', 'id': 11137424, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/11137424?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jomuel', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jomuel/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"The class `DummyTransport` only exists to aid testing, the callbacks are used to save the messages that go through the protocol layer. The current version of the code base has the WAL, which allows for a cleaner way to query all the messages/events that went through the system, so DummyTransport is not necessary anymore.

