17511,IssuesEvent,2018-07-06 13:30:28+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,90851,palango,19666847,raiden-network,closed,REST API updates,"[{'id': 974626989, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NzQ2MjY5ODk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/P2', 'name': 'P2', 'color': '683faf', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'palango', 'id': 90851, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjkwODUx', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/90851?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/palango', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"## Problem Definition

We need to update some parts of the Rest API for the new smart contracts. (ref #1383 )

- [x] `GET /api/<version>/address`: No changes needed
- [x] `PUT /api/<version>/tokens/<token_address>`: Should return `token_network_address` instead of `channel_manager_address`
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/channels/<channel_address>`: `channel_address` is a hash now, input checking will need to be changed
  - [ ] Should probably return the `token_network_address` as well
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/channels`: Should probably return the `token_network_address` for each channel (see above)
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/tokens`: No changes needed
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/tokens/<token_address>/partners`: No changes needed
- [x] `PUT /api/<version>/token_swaps/<target_address>/<identifier>`: Should be removed for red eyes
- [x] `PUT /api/<version>/channels`: No changes needed
- [x] `PATCH /api/<version>/channels/<channel_address>`: `channel_address` is a hash now, input checking will need to be changed
- [x] `PUT /api/<version>/connections/<token_address>`: No changes needed
- [x] `DELETE /api/<version>/connections/<token_address>`: No changes needed
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/connections`: No changes needed
- [x] `POST /api/<version>/transfers/<token_address>/<target_address>`: No changes needed
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/events/network`
  - [x] Should return `token_network_address` instead of `channel_manager_address`
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/events/tokens/<token_address>`
  - [x] Should return `channel_identifier` instead of `netting_channel`
- [x] `GET /api/<version>/events/channels/<channel_registry_address>`: Not called `channel_registry_address`. Should be `token_network_address`. ",{},{}
