17589,IssuesEvent,2017-05-08 15:28:38+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Consequence of external removal of tracked files.,[],"[{'login': 'gaow', 'id': 917985, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/917985?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/gaow', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"#543 raised the issue whether external `rm -rf` should trigger rerun. The current design is that the workflow would skip steps as long as file signatures are present, which is the case for `rm -rf` because that command does not remove signatures. The behavior can be confusing because some times steps seem to be mysteriously skipped.

If we are to trigger rerun with the removal of files, we would need to  change test for `target.exists` from `any` (namely `signature` or `target`) to `target`. This is almost trivial but cause cause the question as how to remove large intermediate files without rerun.

Solution 1: Put signature next to file so that `rm -f file*` would remove `file` and `file.sig` and trigger rerun. In contrast, if a user remove a file without its signature `rm -f file`, the step would skip.

Pros:
1. seems to be easy to understand
Cons:
1. Contaminate file system with signature files.

Solution 2: Use special command to remove file. For example, use command `sos remove file` to replace `file` with `file.sig` in user's file system.

Pros:
1. Less contamination of file system because only files that are replaced with their signatures are different. 
2. This also allows users to remove `.sig` file outside of sos to trigger rerun.

Cons:
1. Special command to replace files with their signatures.




",{},{}
