18069,IssuesEvent,2018-04-09 16:16:39+00:00,72017740,python-security/pyt,22822319,davisjam,23080898,python-security,opened,Suggestion: Detect regexes vulnerable to catastrophic backtracking,[],[],0,"It doesn't look like your scanner checks for regexes vulnerable to catastrophic backtracking (-> REDOS).

To do that you could use some tools I built [here](https://github.com/davisjam/vuln-regex-detector). The underlying detectors incur dependencies (2 rely on Java, one relies on OCaml).

If dependencies are a problem, I am hosting a server that answers queries, see docs and code [here](https://github.com/davisjam/vuln-regex-detector/tree/master/src/cache). This requires shipping regexes to my server though.",{},{}
