18343,IssuesEvent,2017-08-09 20:46:33+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,13318509,Saqibm128,28732122,localstack,opened,SQS fails to create deadqueue/redrive policy,[],[],0,"Happens whether redrive policy attribute is attached when queue is created or if queue is already created and set-queue-attributes is used.

```
aws sqs --endpoint-url http://192.168.99.101:4576 create-queue --queue-name test-dead-queue
aws sqs --endpoint-url http://192.168.99.101:4576 create-queue --queue-name test-queue --attributes '{""RedrivePolicy"": ""{\""deadLetterTargetArn\"":\""arn:aws:sqs:us-east-1:123456789012:test-dead-queue\"",\""maxReceiveCount\"":5}""}'
```
While other attributes will show up, redrivePolicy is missing when we run this command
```
aws sqs --endpoint-url http://192.168.99.101:4576 get-queue-attributes --queue-url http://192.168.99.101:4576/123456789012/test-queue --attribute-names All
```

Similar if we set queue attributes as well

```
aws sqs --endpoint-url http://192.168.99.101:4576 set-attributes --queue-url http://192.168.99.101:4576/123456789012/test-queue --attributes '{""RedrivePolicy"": ""{\""deadLetterTargetArn\"":\""arn:aws:sqs:us-east-1:123456789012:test-dead-queue\"",\""maxReceiveCount\"":5}""}'

aws sqs --endpoint-url http://192.168.99.101:4576 get-queue-attributes --queue-url http://192.168.99.101:4576/123456789012/test-queue --attribute-names All
```",{},{}
